File: `platform/browser-extension/src/side-panel/components/PluginList.tsx`

The current code renders all plugins in a single `<Accordion type="multiple" className="space-y-2">` (line 55-70). Split this into two groups:

```tsx
const readyPlugins = visiblePlugins.filter(p => p.tabState === 'ready');
const notReadyPlugins = visiblePlugins.filter(p => p.tabState !== 'ready');
```

When `filterLower` is non-empty, render the existing single-list behavior (no grouping, no label). When not filtering, render:

```tsx
<>
  {visibleFailed.length > 0 && (
    <div className="mb-3 space-y-2">
      {visibleFailed.map(fp => <FailedPluginCard key={fp.specifier} plugin={fp} />)}
    </div>
  )}
  {readyPlugins.length > 0 && (
    <Accordion type="multiple" className="space-y-2">
      {readyPlugins.map(plugin => <PluginCard ... />)}
    </Accordion>
  )}
  {notReadyPlugins.length > 0 && (
    <div>
      <div className="text-[10px] font-mono text-muted-foreground tracking-widest uppercase px-3 pt-3 pb-1">
        NOT CONNECTED
      </div>
      <Accordion type="multiple" className="space-y-2">
        {notReadyPlugins.map(plugin => <PluginCard ... />)}
      </Accordion>
    </div>
  )}
</>
```

For the not-ready card opacity: add `className` prop passing `'opacity-70'` to the PluginCard's Accordion.Item. Looking at `PluginCard.tsx:120-122`, the className on Accordion.Item already has conditional logic for `removingPlugin`. Extend it to also apply `opacity-70` when `plugin.tabState !== 'ready'`:

```tsx
<Accordion.Item
  value={plugin.name}
  className={
    removingPlugin
      ? 'pointer-events-none opacity-60 transition-opacity'
      : plugin.tabState !== 'ready'
        ? 'opacity-70 transition-opacity'
        : undefined
  }>
```

This opacity change is in PluginCard.tsx, but it's tightly coupled to this story's grouping behavior — the opacity only makes visual sense when cards are grouped.
